{
  "texts": [
    "After choosing trivialisations we obtain Lie algebra isomorphisms (adM 1) b ≃ 𝔫 ≃ (adM 2) f (b) for some given point b ∈ B.",
    "Using parallel transport, the map f ad is in turn completely determined by what it does at the fibre over b, and this action is simply by an automorphism φ ∈ Aut(𝔫).",
    "The condition f * ad h 2 = h 1 translates into φ • h 1 = h 2.",
    "The fibre isomorphisms with 𝔫 also yield explicit holonomy representations ρ 1: π 1 (B, b) → Aut(𝔫) and ρ 2: π 1 (B, f (b)) → Aut(𝔫), and it is easy to check that φ must satisfy the compatibility condition φρ1 ([γ])φ -1 = ρ 2 ([ f • γ]) for all [γ] ∈ π 1 (B, b).Suppose now that two triples are equivalent as per 23.",
    "Then, the above observations imply that the corresponding solitons are isometric via a bundle map.Conversely, suppose that there is an isometric bundle map determined by f and φ as above."
  ]
}